    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Term for all members of the subfamily Threskiornithinae that do not have a spoonbill. They are medium-sized wading birds who inhabit shallow lagoons, lakes, bays, and marshes and use their slender, down-curved bills to feed on small fishes and soft mollusks.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
